<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10319&amp;p=116651#p116651"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: GBA Flash carts]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10319&amp;p=116651#p116651"><![CDATA[
A NAND device would still have to copy the game to RAM to run it. It just acts as if it were a raw NAND needing a software controller, like a SmartMedia or xD-Picture card as opposed to CF or SD. Only NOR flash is word-addressed in the way that allows for the sort of execute-in-place operation needed to run programs without copying them to RAM first. Most cards that are 512 Mbit or smaller are NOR based.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Aug 17, 2013 9:34 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
