<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: GBA Flash carts]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10319&amp;p=115880#p115880"><![CDATA[
The SuperCard is a let down for GBA. I owned one before. As you noticed, basically all games must be patched due to the Slow RAM (or Memory Controller) in the product not being able to keep up with *normal* ROM speeds. The pre-fetch does not make up for this. Games that normally don't suffer slowdown will. Some games suffer terrible slowdowns. The SuperCard is more useful for playing NDS games. I recommend if you can find one, one of the M3 Adapters. While any GBA device requires patching the ROMs if they use something other than SRAM it's not a bit deal. SuperCard's the one that *really* requires patching not just for saving but for not crashing when the RAM can't keep up. <br /><br />I'd highly recommend trying to find another product.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Tue Jul 30, 2013 1:48 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
