I own a SuperCard CF version, and haven't noticed any issues. IIRC, the patching is done at least in part to allow things like realtime saving, which I assume that it does by installing its own interrupt handler that does whatever it needs to do and then calls the original handler. Last time I used the PC tool, I think it would look up the ROMs in some kind of database to know how to patch the them. If no match was found - e.g. if I added my own techdemos - it would say something like &quot;Patching failed&quot; and supposedly not modify the ROM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1181">mic_</a> — Thu Jul 25, 2013 2:01 pm</p><hr />
